Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/dom/element.c
+++ b/ext/dom/element.c
@@ -713,10 +713,18 @@
 	nsp = attrp->ns;
-	if (use_ns && nsp != NULL) {
-		existattrp = xmlHasNsProp(nodep, attrp->name, nsp->href);
-	} else {
-		existattrp = xmlHasProp(nodep, attrp->name);
-	}
+	if (use_ns && nsp != NULL) {
+		if (nsp->href == NULL) {
+			php_dom_throw_error(INVALID_CHARACTER_ERR, dom_get_strict_error(intern->document));
+			RETURN_FALSE;
+		}
+		existattrp = xmlHasNsProp(nodep, attrp->name, nsp->href);
+	} else {
+		existattrp = xmlHasProp(nodep, attrp->name);
+	}
 '}`
responded: The root cause of the null dereference is in this line:
```c
existattrp = xmlHasNsProp(nodep, attrp->name, nsp->href);
```
If `nsp` is not NULL but `nsp->href` is NULL, this will dereference a NULL pointer, causing a crash.

**Fix:**  
Before calling `xmlHasNsProp(nodep, attrp->name, nsp->href)`, we must check that `nsp->href` is not NULL. If it is NULL, we should handle it gracefully (e.g., throw an error or return).

Let's generate a patch that adds this check.

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/element.c b/ext/dom/element.c
index b4495559830..5ac2b1a97a4 100644
--- a/ext/dom/element.c
+++ b/ext/dom/element.c
@@ -712,6 +712,10 @@ static void dom_element_set_attribute_node_common(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS,

 	nsp = attrp->ns;
 	if (use_ns && nsp != NULL) {
